==English==

===Etymology===
Middle French ''piquant'' "pricking, stimulating, irritating".

===Adjective===
'''piquant'''

# [[engaging|Engaging]]; [[charming]].
# Favorably [[stimulating]] to the [[palate]]; pleasantly [[spicy]]; stimulating.
# (archaic) Causing hurt feelings; [[scathing]].

